During Antibiotic Awareness Week, the article highlights the threat of antibiotic resistance to public health. It emphasizes the importance of appropriate prescribing and use of antibiotics by medical professionals, veterinarians, and researchers. Antibiotics have played a crucial role in modern healthcare, but antibiotic resistance limits their effectiveness, leading to difficult-to-cure infections and thousands of deaths in the US each year. The National Action Plan for Combating Antibiotic-Resistant Bacteria is mentioned as a strategy to identify resistance, stop its spread, and improve antibiotic use. The article encourages collaboration with international partners and the development of new vaccines, diagnostic tests, and medications. Ultimately, it urges patients and doctors to only use antibiotics when necessary and as directed. The author calls on Americans to educate themselves about antibiotic resistance and take action to address this public health issue.